title: Inside the Huddle with Jim Harbaugh
text:
Previous Next 
(WXYZ) - Brad Galli sat down with Michigan Head Football Coach Jim Harbaugh on Monday afternoon after the team's 38-0 victory over Northwestern. The interview is also ahead of the top-12 matchup against in-state rival Michigan State on Saturday. 
Harbaugh quoted "The Lion King" during the interview while discussing the past history with Michigan State. 
Also, Harbaugh said he was impressed by Michigan State and quarterback Connor Cook. 
As for the Spartans defense, Harbaugh said it's only Monday, but he is still trying to get a first down on the veteran defense. 
After three straight shutouts, the Wolverines' defense has been the talk of all media outlets, but he is not ready to say the team's identity is its defense. 
You can catch Inside the Huddle with Jim Harbaugh every Monday on 7 Action News at 6.
